  "meta": {
    "description": "Semantic alias lists for each causal pathway. These phrases are appended to the evidence card text before embedding with nomic-embed-text, so that broad or indirect user queries activate the correct cards via cosine similarity. Each alias list covers: (1) the exact causal pathway vocabulary, (2) colloquial and field-worker phrasings, (3) production system umbrella terms, (4) symptom descriptions a user might mention, (5) intervention vocabulary that implies the problem, (6) social-ecological and cross-cutting terms.",
    "usage": "At evidence card generation time, concatenate the card's overall_reasoning_note with the aliases string (space-separated or as a short paragraph) before calling nomic-embed-text. At query time, embed only the raw user query — do not augment it. The asymmetry is intentional: the card side is enriched, the query side is left as-is.",
    "format": "Each entry has pathway_id (matching diagnosis_framework.json), production_system, and aliases (list of short phrases). The aliases are designed to be appended as a single paragraph: 'Related themes: <alias1>. <alias2>. ...'",
    "note_on_length": "Keep each alias list to 20–35 phrases. Too many aliases dilute the embedding toward the centre of the semantic space and reduce discrimination. Prioritise phrases that are semantically distant from the card's core text but likely to appear in real queries."
  },
